Happy 30th Birthday To The Most Loving Son Ever! I can’t believe you turn 30 years old today! It’s so bitter sweet to look at your baby pics. I just can’t believe it. Here’s to the guy who hates when I call him “baby” and who hates when I post baby pics. I cannot believe I had you 30 years ago today. 

I never got to take a picture with you in the hospital on January 16, 1993 so I will always cherish the very first photo we ever took together…when you were 1 week old. 

I love you with all my heart and I’m so proud of the man that you are today. Enjoy this ride through life. You deserve all the happiness in the world. We all love you so much! Happy Happy 30th to my one and only. I love you..You will always be my BABY! @gerodchristian

Birthday in Bermuda 🇧🇲

Last year I turned 50. It didn’t hit me until I turned 51 how much time is just flying by. Who would’ve ever known that by age 51 you still wouldn’t be perfect, you still would have a lot to learn, and there’s still so much more to do. 

It’s a trip how my mind and my body has changed and how you experience a different journey each year that passes. Yearly mammograms have always been so important. And of course that first colonoscopy. I got married at 48 years old and menopause set in on my wedding day. My one and only child turned 30 years old. I always thought I would have more children. Crazy how life is. 

Being a waitress & a bartender was hard, having a baby was hard, being a personal trainer was hard, Polynesian dancing was hard (owning my own Polynesian dance group was harder), nursing school was hard, being a nurse was hard, owning a medical spa was hard, becoming an entrepreneur was hard…today I’m working just as hard. And I would do it all over again! 

I’m still trying to become the best person I can be…for my family, my friends, younger women, young girls, my husband and for myself. Every day I have to MOTIVATE ME in order to be the best I can be. I’m ready, blessed & so happy to take on the next half of my life. There’s so much more to do and more to come. 
Thank you all for the amazing birthday wishes! 🩷
